question:
District category contains Housing Estate, Senior Living Community, and Historic Neighborhood.
Supermarkets category contains Big Lots, Thrive Market, and Safeway.
The number of each Housing Estate 's Thrive Market equals the difference of each Senior Living Community 's Supermarkets and each Historic Neighborhood 's Big Lots.
The number of each Senior Living Community 's Thrive Market equals each Historic Neighborhood 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Historic Neighborhood 's Big Lots equals 11.
How many Supermarkets does Housing Estate have?
solution:
Define each Historic Neighborhood 's Big Lots as x; So x = 11.
Define each Historic Neighborhood 's Supermarkets as y; So y = x = 11.
Define each Senior Living Community 's Thrive Market as U; So U = y = 11.
Define each Senior Living Community 's Supermarkets as R; So R = U = 11.
Define each Housing Estate 's Thrive Market as V; So V = R - x = 11 - 11 = 0.
Define each Housing Estate 's Supermarkets as j; So j = V = 0.
